\begin_layout Section

\lang english
Supply Chain Risk Management (SCRM) and Vendor Governance
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "pol:1.13"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Policy Metadata

\lang english
Effective:
 July 01,
 2026
\begin_inset space \hfill{}
\end_inset

Version:
 1.0
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes a consistent and enforceable governance framework for the engagement,
 onboarding,
 oversight,
 and offboarding of third-party service providers,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 and consultants.
 It incorporates Supply Chain Risk Management (SCRM) principles to identify and mitigate risks associated with the acquisition of technology products and services.
 Its primary objective is to ensure that external entities interacting with Elko County information systems adhere to the same security,
 privacy,
 and operational standards required of County personnel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all third-party entities,
 including vendors,
 contractors,
 consultants,
 and managed service providers (MSPs),
 who:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Are granted physical or logical access to County IT assets,
 facilities,
 or systems;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Provide hardware,
 software,
 or cloud-based solutions integrated with County operations;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Require network connectivity (on-premise,
 VPN,
 or cloud integration);
 or
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Store,
 process,
 transmit,
 or administer Elko County data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Exclusion
\series default
:
 This policy does not apply to commodity off-the-shelf (COTS) consumables (e.g.,
 toner,
 cables) where the vendor has no access to County systems,
 data,
 or secure facilities.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the Technical Authority.
 Shall validate technical scope,
 approve architectural fit,
 define security boundaries,
 and reject vendors that fail to meet minimum security requirements or refuse required security addendums.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Requesting Department Head
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the Relationship Manager.
 Shall define business requirements,
 fund the engagement,
 manage vendor deliverables/timelines,
 and ensure vendor adherence to County operational requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Human Resources
\series default
:
 Shall maintain personnel tracking for individual contractors requiring system access and shall coordinate required background screening processes where applicable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Fiscal Affairs
\series default
:
 Shall ensure contracts include County-required indemnification and procurement clauses and shall verify CJIS contract requirements are applied when CJI may be accessed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mandatory Compliance
\series default
:
 Adherence to this policy is mandatory for all third-party interactions involving County information systems or data.
 Unauthorized provisioning of access or assets to a third party is a security violation subject to corrective action under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Unauthorized Commitments (“Shadow IT”)
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Information Operations Department shall not integrate,
 onboard,
 or support technology acquired without documented Technical Approval.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Fiscal Affairs shall not process payment for technology purchases or subscriptions without documented Technical Approval,
 in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.10"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (“No Registration,
 No Pay”).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Requesting Department shall fund remediation,
 replacement,
 and incident-response costs resulting from unauthorized technology commitments.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions shall be requested in writing,
 documented with justification,
 reviewed by the IT Director,
 and approved in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


